      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Outdoor photograph of a group of three men in official military uniforms with insignias of honour on a red carpet. There are many men in military uniforms and in urban clothes on either side of them.</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Official welcome in Vidin after the coronation of Ferdinand as Prince/Knyaz of Bulgaria. Ferdinand I, born Ferdinand Maximilian Karl Leopold Maria of Saxe-Coburg and Gotha-Koháry, ruled Bulgaria from 1887 to 1918, first as Knyaz (Prince Regnant, 1887–1908) and later as Tsar (1908–1918). Among the officials in the picture are G. Zivkov, D. Colakov, K. Stoilov, St. Stambolov, and S. Mutkurov.</ab>
